user_review: The most amazing authentic Lebanese food we've had. Family run operation, so service is a bit slow but the food more than makes up for it. Every dish we got was just delicious, the flavors were so fresh.
There's nowhere better to go for great food and great service. Support small business and dine here!

First impressions: cosy and family-owned, authentic. We experienced very customized and attentive service by the owner who patiently answered our questions and offered great suggestions. We had the vegetarian mezze and all the dishes were super tasty (especially the falafels and the baba ganouj). For dessert, we had a custard with pistachio and rose water: it was amazing, very flavourful and not too sweet (and imagine our delight when we found out it was on the house, wow!)Highly recommended.
Great food, kind owner/server. A little pricy but would definitely recommend, it's worth it!

Absolutely delicious food with that home-made Middle Eastern taste.  The server/owner was very gracious and helpful and made us feel very welcome.  The Fattoush salad had wonderful dressing, and both humus and baba ghanouj were delicious.  Fried cheese (sanbousek?) was divine, and the Chicken Lilas very tasty was well.  Both the desert, a kind of pudding and baklava, were 10 out of 10.  Don't miss this neighborhood gem that is small and cosy, very clean and inviting, and very reasonable prices as well.
